    },
    {
      "_type": "block",
      "style": "normal",
      "children": [
        {
          "_type": "span",
          "text": "Most people are going to default to “great” or “bad” or “alright” habitually.",
          "marks": []
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "_type": "block",
      "style": "normal",
      "children": [
        {
          "_type": "span",
          "text": "And because the question itself doesn’t have any constraints, it’s hard to know (or articulate) what to say.",
          "marks": []
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "_type": "block",
      "style": "normal",
      "children": [
        {
          "_type": "span",
          "text": "Here’s a better alternative: What are three things we can improve?",
          "marks": []
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "_type": "block",
      "style": "normal",
      "children": [
        {
          "_type": "span",
          "text": "Almost everyone can tell you a few ways they’d improve your product, service or experience.",
          "marks": []
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "_type": "block",
      "style": "normal",
      "children": [
        {
          "_type": "span",
          "text": "And because you’re not asking them to gauge how they feel, you’ll actually get feedback you can use and implement straightaway.",
          "marks": []
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "_type": "block",
      "style": "normal",
      "children": [
        {
          "_type": "span",
          "text": "Explicit questions are how you avoid vague (meaningless) answers.",
          "marks": []
        }
      ]
    }
  ]
}